This paper deals with evaluation metrics for generative models, specifically in the context of GANs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the Inception network, which is commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting a possible fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a method for improving estimates using Quasi-Monte Carlo integration, which is a numerical analysis technique, potentially fitting into cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper discusses bias in evaluation metrics, which is a topic relevant to the broader field of Artificial Intelligence, potentially fitting into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
